Popular gospel singer, Lanre Teriba, Atorise, is set to give his fans a memorable time on his tour of the United States of America which is set to commence soon. Tagged, ‘Breakthrough’, the singer stated that the tour will commence in May and take him to 21 cities in USA. According to a statement sent to Merrymakers, Atorise stated that the tour will kick off in Houston, Texas, to celebrate the Memorial Day weekend. He will then ‘continue to spread the gospel of his music at the Summer 2022 African Pop-Up Festival in New York’, which is produced by a Nigerian, Akin Akinsanya, in celebration of African music, food and culture. Regarded as an ‘evergreen product’, the singer noted that various promoters in the US have also booked him to perform at concerts in Indianapolis, Minneapolis, Chicago, Dallas, Miami, Philadelphia and other cities across the North American country. Teriba started his music career in 1999 and has grown to become one of the leading lights of Yoruba ‘tungba’ gospel music. His hit track, Atorise, from which he got his nickname, is regarded as an evergreen song.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com